posts.post_title: FS: N173 Cabinet Proof Hank Gastright Gilbert and Bacon Studio
posts.post_content:
Hello Collectors,

I have a fantastic 1889 N173 Cabinet Proof of Hank Gastright of the Columbus Solons. This proof was produced by the Gilbert and Bacon Studio. There is a small nick to the upper left hand corner but overall the cabinet is in very good shape. The image is strong and the back features only light toning but no major problems. Gastright won 30 games for Solons in 1890.

I'm looking to sell for $850. Please pm me if interested.

[IMG]http://i107.photobucket.com/albums/m294/madjams/N173Proof_zpsbb46047a.jpg[/IMG]
Thanks for posting. Really appreciate it.

posts.post_title: FS: N173 Cabinet Proof Hank Gastright Gilbert and Bacon Studio
posts.post_content: I can't go $950, but if you want to talk let me know. Would fit nicely with my Columbus Solons OJ team set.
Bump. This cabinet now resides in an SGC 10 holder.
